title: Anterior & Lateral Compartments of the Leg, Dorsum of Foot

questions.question: 1. Which nerve supplies the muscles of the anterior compartment of the leg?
2. Which muscle is the primary dorsiflexor of the foot in the anterior compartment?
3. Which muscle extends the lateral four toes in the anterior compartment?
4. Which muscle is responsible for extension of the great toe?
5. Which muscle in the anterior compartment is sometimes considered part of both the anterior and lateral groups due to its role in dorsiflexion and eversion?
6. Which artery supplies the anterior compartment of the leg?
7. Which nerve supplies the muscles of the lateral compartment of the leg?
8. Which muscle in the lateral compartment is primarily responsible for eversion of the foot?
9. Which muscle in the lateral compartment plays a key role in both plantarflexion and eversion of the foot?
10. What is the primary sensory distribution of the superficial fibular nerve?
options: Most of the dorsum of the foot
The web space between the first and second toes
The lateral aspect of the leg
The medial aspect of the foot

questions.question: 11. Which tendon serves as a landmark for palpating the dorsalis pedis artery on the dorsum of the foot?
12. The dorsalis pedis artery is the continuation of which artery?
13. Which nerve provides sensory innervation to the web space between the great toe and the second toe?
14. The tendons of which muscle group are located in the lateral compartment of the leg?
15. Which muscle wraps around the lateral malleolus and supports the transverse arch of the foot?
